PowerShell-Function-Show-EdgeTabsGrouped @"
Perfect ‚Äî let‚Äôs build a PowerShell function that will **collect tab data from JSON, group them by domain, and print them with `Write-Host`**. This way you can quickly see which tabs belong to the same site (e.g., all `file://E:/QuranerFariwala` grouped together, all `bing.com` grouped together).

---

## PowerShell Function

```powershell
function Show-EdgeTabsGrouped {
    <#
    .SYNOPSIS
        Displays Edge browser tabs grouped by domain.
    .DESCRIPTION
        Accepts a JSON array of tab metadata (pageTitle, pageUrl, tabId, isCurrent).
        Groups tabs by domain (host portion of URL or local path root).
        Prints each group with Write-Host, highlighting the current tab.
    .PARAMETER Json
        The JSON string containing tab metadata.
    #>

    param(
        [Parameter(Mandatory=$true)]
        [string]$Json
    )

    # Convert JSON string to objects
    $tabs = $Json | ConvertFrom-Json

    # Helper: extract domain or root folder from URL
    function Get-DomainOrRoot($url) {
        try {
            $uri = [Uri]$url
            if ($uri.Scheme -eq "file") {
                # For file:// paths, take the first folder after drive
                $segments = $uri.AbsolutePath.Split("/")
                if ($segments.Length -gt 2) {
                    return "$($uri.Scheme)://$($segments[1])"
                } else {
                    return "$($uri.Scheme)://local"
                }
            } else {
                return $uri.Host
            }
        } catch {
            return "unknown"
        }
    }

    # Group tabs by domain/root
    $groups = $tabs | Group-Object { Get-DomainOrRoot $_.pageUrl }

    foreach ($group in $groups) {
        Write-Host "=========================================" -ForegroundColor Cyan
        Write-Host "Domain/Root: $($group.Name)" -ForegroundColor Yellow
        Write-Host "-----------------------------------------" -ForegroundColor Cyan

        foreach ($tab in $group.Group) {
            if ($tab.isCurrent -eq $true) {
                Write-Host "ACTIVE TAB:" -ForegroundColor Green
                Write-Host "  Title : $($tab.pageTitle)" -ForegroundColor Green
                Write-Host "  URL   : $($tab.pageUrl)" -ForegroundColor Green
                Write-Host "  TabId : $($tab.tabId)" -ForegroundColor Green
                Write-Host ""
            }
            else {
                Write-Host "Background Tab:" -ForegroundColor White
                Write-Host "  Title : $($tab.pageTitle)" -ForegroundColor White
                Write-Host "  URL   : $($tab.pageUrl)" -ForegroundColor White
                Write-Host "  TabId : $($tab.tabId)" -ForegroundColor White
                Write-Host ""
            }
        }
    }
}
```

