PowerShell-Function-Show-Roadmap1 @"
Here‚Äôs a PowerShell function that can act as a **roadmap viewer with progress bars**. It takes JSON data describing roadmap items (milestones, tasks, goals) and prints them out with `Write-Host`, showing a simple text‚Äëbased progress bar and percentage completion.

---

## PowerShell Function

```powershell
function Show-Roadmap {
    <#
    .SYNOPSIS
        Displays a roadmap (milestones, tasks, goals) with progress bars.
    .DESCRIPTION
        Accepts a JSON array of roadmap items with fields like Title, Description, Owner, DueDate, Status, Progress.
        Prints each item with Write-Host, showing a progress bar and percentage completion.
    .PARAMETER Json
        The JSON string containing roadmap items.
    #>

    param(
        [Parameter(Mandatory=$true)]
        [string]$Json
    )

    # Convert JSON string to objects
    $items = $Json | ConvertFrom-Json

    Write-Host "========== ROADMAP ==========" -ForegroundColor Cyan

    foreach ($item in $items) {
        Write-Host "----------------------------------------" -ForegroundColor Cyan
        Write-Host "Milestone : $($item.Title)" -ForegroundColor Yellow
        if ($item.Description) { Write-Host "Details   : $($item.Description)" -ForegroundColor White }
        if ($item.Owner)       { Write-Host "Owner     : $($item.Owner)" -ForegroundColor Green }
        if ($item.DueDate)     { Write-Host "Due Date  : $($item.DueDate)" -ForegroundColor DarkCyan }
        if ($item.Status)      { Write-Host "Status    : $($item.Status)" -ForegroundColor Magenta }

        # Progress bar
        if ($item.Progress -ne $null) {
            $percent = [int]$item.Progress
            $barLength = 20
            $filled = [int]($barLength * $percent / 100)
            $empty = $barLength - $filled
            $bar = ("#" * $filled) + ("-" * $empty)
            Write-Host ("Progress : [{0}] {1}%" -f $bar, $percent) -ForegroundColor DarkYellow
        }
    }

    Write-Host "========================================" -ForegroundColor Cyan
}
